<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>PyVideo.org</title><link>https://pyvideo.org/</link><description></description><atom:link href="https://pyvideo.org/feeds/speaker_eyal-trabelsi.rss.xml" rel="self"></atom:link><lastBuildDate>Thu, 23 Jul 2020 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>Elegant Exception Handling</title><link>https://pyvideo.org/europython-2020/elegant-exception-handling.html</link><description>&lt;h3&gt;Description&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Error handling is hard. Regardless of the approach you take, it usually means littering your application with checks and validations that greatly reduce code readability. So how can we tackle exceptions?&lt;/p&gt;
